SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ENDOWMENT FUNDS THE NET INCOME FROM THE DONOR ADVISED ENDOWMENTS IS DISTRIBUTED TO QUALIFIED CHARITIES AT THE DIRECTION OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, AFTER CONSIDERATION OF DONOR RECOMMENDATIONS.

FIN 48 FOOTNOTE THE ORGANIZATION IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THE ORGANIZATION RECOGNIZES THE EFFECT OF INCOME TAX POSITIONS ONLY IF THOSE POSITIONS ARE MORE LIKELY THAN NOT OF BEING SUSTAINED. SUCH TAX POSITIONS, WHICH ARE MORE THAN 50% LIKELY OF BEING REALIZED, ARE MEASURED AT THEIR HIGHEST VALUE. CHANGES IN RECOGNITION OR MEASUREMENT ARE REFLECTED IN THE PERIOD IN WHICH THE CHANGE IN JUDGMENT OCCURS. DURING FISCAL YEARS 2018 AND 2017, MANAGEMENT DETERMINED THAT THERE ARE NO INCOME TAX POSITIONS REQUIRING RECOGNITION IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MONITORING OF GRANT FUNDS For donor advised funds, donors are required to submit a grant recommendation form stating the recommended charity and the recommended grant amount. Once verified that the charity is a 501(c)(3) charity in good standing, the recommendation is voted upon by the board of directors. For charitable accounts, staff reviews requests for payment and verifies the appropriateness of the expenses.

COMPENSATION OFFICERS SPEND A SUBSTANTIAL AMOUNT OF THEIR TIME WORKING FOR THE UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA FOUNDATION, A RELATED ORGANIZATION, AND THEIR COMPENSATION IS REVIEWED BY THIS ORGANIZATION. THE UNF CHARITABLE GIFT FUND DOES NOT COMPENSATE A CEO, EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, KEY EMPLOYEES, OR ANY TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL.
ELECTION OF BOARD OF DIRECTORS THE ELECTION OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF THE UNF CHARITABLE GIFT FUND IS SUBJECT TO APPROVAL BY THE UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA FOUNDATION.

GOVERNANCE The Articles of Incorporation and bylaws of the UNF Charitable Gift Fund grant control of its Board to the Board of Directors of the University of Nebraska Foundation, a related organization. University of Nebraska Foundation appoints and approves the Board of Directors for UNF Charitable Gift Fund, there are no overlapping members.
FORM 990 REVIEW THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE OFFICERS OF THE ORGANIZATION PRIOR TO FILING AND A FINAL COPY WITH SCHEDULE B REDACTED IS GIVEN TO THE BOARD PRIOR TO THE TIME OF FILING.

CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ANNUAL COMPLETION OF THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST DISCLOSURE IS REQUIRED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND ALL OFFICERS OF THE UNF CHARITABLE GIFT FUND. STATED CONFLICTS ARE INVESTIGATED BY IN-HOUSE LEGAL COUNSEL AND REPORTED TO THE CHAIR OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE CHAIR REVIEWS ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS AND MAKES A RECOMMENDATION TO THE BOARD, IF APPROPRIATE. THE BOARD MAKES THE FINAL DETERMINATION OF WHETHER OR NOT THERE IS A DISQUALIFYING EVENT. AT ANY TIME, A BOARD MEMBER MAY DECLARE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST AND RECUSE HIMSELF/HERSELF FROM THE DISCUSSION. THE INDIVIDUAL IS ALSO REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE ANY KNOWN OR POSSIBLE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST THAT ARISE DURING THE CALENDAR YEAR.
COMPENSATION REVIEW THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT COMPENSATE A CEO, EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, OFFICERS, KEY EMPLOYEES OR ANY TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL. THESE QUESTIONS HAVE BEEN MARKED NO PER THE INSTRUCTIONS.
GOVERNING DOCUMENTS THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.

AUDIT OVERSIGHT AS OF JULY 1, 2015, THE ORGANIZATION AMENDED ITS ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION AND BYLAWS TO GRANT CONTROL OF ITS BOARD OF DIRECTORS TO THE UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA FOUNDATION. THE FOUNDATION ACCOUNTED FOR THE CHANGE IN CONTROL AS A CHANGE IN REPORTING ENTITY FOR FINANCIAL REPORTING PURPOSES. AS SUCH THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS OF THE ORGANIZATION WERE CONSOLIDATED WITH THE FOUNDATION'S 2016 FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND WILL CONTINUE TO BE CONSOLIDATED IN SUBSEQUENT YEARS. THE FOUNDATION HAS AN AUDIT COMMITTEE THAT ASSUMES RESPONSIBILITY FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT AND SELECTION OF THE INDEPENDENT AUDITOR.
